      "writtenOn": "2026-05-28T12:49:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It is actually checking whether anything exists after `+grep/`.\nAt this point `path` is still the raw command tail, not the final repository path.\n\n\nFor example -\n\n1. `/repo/+grep/master` -\n    ```\n    raw path to parse: master\n    revision: master\n    repo path: empty\n    meaning: grep from the repository root\n    ```\n\n2. `/repo/+grep/master/src` -\n    ```\n    raw path to parse: master/src\n    revision: master\n    repo path: src\n    meaning: grep only src/\n    ```\n\n3. `/repo/+grep/`\n    ```\n    raw path to parse: empty\n    meaning: invalid, because no revision was given\n    ```\n\n\nSo this rejects only URLs without a revision, such as `/repo/+grep` or `/repo/+grep/`.",
      "parentUuid": "4a101f95_e10cb9b0",
      "range": {
